place.name: WILLERSEY
place.gazetteerText: WILLERSEY, a parish, with a village, in the district of Evesham and-county of Gloucester; 3½ miles W of Chipping-Campden r. station. Post town, Broadway. Acres, 1,344. Real property, £2,522. Pop., 373. Houses, 88. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Gloucester. Value, £180.* Patron, the Rev. J. H. Worgan. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
